                <zone forceUpdate='true' h='18375' id='15' type-v2='text' w='98400' x='800' y='80625'>
                  <formatted-text>
                    <run bold='true' fontalignment='0'>Key Insights</run>
                    <run fontalignment='0'>
• Overall attrition rate is 16.12%, meaning approximately one in six employees leaving the organization.
• Turnover is concentrated within specific departments and job roles, indicating that retention issues are not organization-wide.
• High employee turnover in key operational roles may increase recruitment costs, training expenses, and productivity loss.
• Targeted retention initiatievs are likely to deliver greater impact than broad workforce-wide programs.
</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontalignment='0'>Recommendations</run>
                    <run fontalignment='0'>
• Prioritize retention efforts in high-attrition departments and roles.
• Review workload and career progression opportunities in high-turnover departments.
• Establish regular monitoring of attrition KPIs to proactively identify workforce risks.</run>
                  </formatted-text>
                  <zone-style>
                    <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                    <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                    <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                    <format attr='margin' value='4' />
                    <format attr='padding' value='0' />
                  </zone-style>
